your binoculars.

00:08.301 --> 00:11.259
A Iepidopterist without binoculars
is like a day without sunshine.

00:11.345 --> 00:13.176
Guess I was nervous
to meet you.

00:13.264 --> 00:16.176
I’ve never done
the “online date” thing before.

00:16.267 --> 00:18.633
[ Man ] There’s
a Red-banded Hairstreak.
It’s so beautiful.

00:18.728 --> 00:20.844
Look what’s next to it.

00:21.856 --> 00:23.642
Right.
Another butterfly.

00:23.733 --> 00:26.065
- Hackberry Emperor.
- Of course.

00:26.152 --> 00:29.064
- Guess I’m just tired.
- You’ve only been at it for a few hours.

00:29.155 --> 00:31.988
When you e-mailed me
and said you were into butterflies,

00:32.074 --> 00:35.612
it sounded romantic,
not like school.

00:37.079 --> 00:40.321
- You’re not really
a lepidopterist, are you?
- No, Gary.

00:40.416 --> 00:43.078
I’m just a woman
looking for a man.

00:43.836 --> 00:46.043
Oh.
Yeah.

00:46.130 --> 00:48.997
- And I brought a blanket.
- Fantastic!

00:49.091 --> 00:52.925
Look at these.
Oh, look at these.

00:53.054 --> 00:56.137
A swarm
of Silvery Checkerspots.
Oh, my God.

00:57.308 --> 01:00.471
This is romantic.

01:00.561 --> 01:03.894
But you’re gonna remember this
a lot more than those butterflies, Gary.

01:03.981 --> 01:07.394
[ Chuckles, Grunts]
Yeah.

01:07.485 --> 01:10.443
- They don’t usually swarm like this.
- Neither do |.

01:16.494 --> 01:19.986
[ Screaming ]

01:23.459 --> 01:25.541
I hate online dating.

01:28.547 --> 01:30.412
[ People Chattering ]

01:30.508 --> 01:33.625
[ Brennan ]
Partially skeletonized.
Ribs splayed open.

01:33.719 --> 01:35.710
l have a feeling
this wasn’t natural causes.

01:35.846 --> 01:37.837
Animal or psycho?
Probably.

01:37.932 --> 01:40.639
The angle of the mandible
and the brow of the skull...

01:40.726 --> 01:43.638
indicate a male
around 40 to 50,

01:43.729 --> 01:46.471
judging by the wear
on the mandibular teeth.

01:46.607 --> 01:50.270
Hey, what’s— what’s with
all the butterflies?
Chlosyne nycz‘e/s.

01:50.361 --> 01:53.774
They’re the Silvery Checkerspot,
indigenous to the area.

01:53.906 --> 01:56.397
They’re probably just
attracted by the remains.
Whoa, whoa, wait.

01:56.534 --> 01:58.741
Butterflies eat
dead people?
Yeah.

01:58.828 --> 02:00.534
Hey, they may look beautiful,

02:00.621 --> 02:03.454
but they’ll eat bird excrement
and aphid guts,

02:03.541 --> 02:05.497
decomposing meat.

02:05.584 --> 02:07.085
Oh. Right.

02:07.169 --> 02:10.127
- What the hell?
- [ Sniffs]

02:10.214 --> 02:12.250
Something smells
like sulfur.

02:12.341 --> 02:15.504
It’s coming from the remains.
lt’s— [ Sniffs]

02:15.594 --> 02:17.585
- [ Sniffing ]
- I hate when you do that.

02:17.680 --> 02:22.140
It’s not a typical odor
associated with decomposition.
[ Sniffs ]

02:22.268 --> 02:23.974
[ Bleating ]
Who would leave
a goat out here?

02:24.061 --> 02:26.393
Who cares about a goat, okay?
We’re dealing with a dead body here.

02:26.480 --> 02:29.142
- Look, shouldn’t there be more blood?
- Yes.

02:29.233 --> 02:31.565
It appears all of the blood has been
drained from the victim’s body.

02:31.652 --> 02:33.563
l’m guessin’ psycho.

02:33.654 --> 02:36.566
[ Brennan ]
But look at the ribs,
two through six, on the left side.

02:36.657 --> 02:38.693
- Bite marks.
- Cannibal?

02:38.784 --> 02:40.399
No. l-lt’s not
human dentition.

02:40.494 --> 02:43.702
- I’m confused.
- Me too. And I don’t like the feeling.

02:43.789 --> 02:45.074
[ Bleating Continues]

02:48.419 --> 02:50.501
So the heart is gone?

02:50.588 --> 02:53.204
Well, it’s like someone ate it
right out of his chest.

02:53.299 --> 02:54.584
[ Hodgins ]
Wow.

02:54.675 --> 02:58.588
The victim’s right ankle has
a vertical transarticular pin...

02:58.679 --> 03:01.762
