downward spiral in the aftermath
of my Jeopardy! win.

03:20.743 --> 03:23.860
- Whoa.
- I had no idea you were in AA.

03:23.954 --> 03:28.118
Yes, well, as with
everything else, discretion
has been my watchword...

03:28.209 --> 03:30.791
except when l was vomiting
into someone’s hat.

03:30.878 --> 03:35.747
- [ Groans ]
- These look like spiny bristles
from some kind of animal.

03:35.841 --> 03:41.256
Oh, and the evidence on the X-rays
shows bone damage on the ribs...

03:41.347 --> 03:43.463
from long, fang-like teeth.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.639
Oh. Maybe the heart
was eaten.

03:45.726 --> 03:48.968
But anyway, um, I’m currently
at step nine of 12,

03:49.105 --> 03:53.644
which consists of me making
amends to those people that I’ve
harmed while I’ve been drinking.

03:53.734 --> 03:56.066
Not necessary.
Don’t even remember being wronged.

03:56.153 --> 03:59.020
l urinated
in your tadpole tank,
Dr. Hodgins.

03:59.115 --> 04:01.322
- What?
- Mr. Nigel-Murray,
that’s disgusting.

04:01.409 --> 04:02.899
Of course.

04:02.993 --> 04:05.985
Anyway, Dr. Hodgins,
I apologize.

04:07.498 --> 04:08.954
Dr. Saroyan.
No.

04:09.041 --> 04:11.828
All I wanna hear from you right now
are facts about this case.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.085
Okay. At this point,
from all of the evidence...

04:15.172 --> 04:16.912
that I’ve gathered
from the X-rays...

04:17.007 --> 04:19.259
as well as the observable
evidence on the remains—

04:19.343 --> 04:23.928
indicates that our victim
was killed by a cryptid.

04:24.014 --> 04:28.758
- Cryptid?
- A creature yet unrecognized
by scientific consensus.

04:28.853 --> 04:30.389
Of course!

04:30.479 --> 04:33.221
Oh, no. You guys
aren’t gonna start talking
about werewolves, are you?

04:33.315 --> 04:36.773
Oh, no, no, no.
I would posit that
it was a chupacabra.

04:36.861 --> 04:40.274
- [ Hodgins ] Oh!
- A spiny creature the size of a bear.

04:40.364 --> 04:45.358
Vicious, forked tongued,
with fangs easily capable of
biting out the victim’s heart.

04:47.371 --> 04:50.955
But no one has ever captured
or verified this chupacabra.

04:51.041 --> 04:54.829
No, but reports show that it
sucks out its victim’s blood...

04:54.920 --> 04:57.536
and leaves behind
the scent of sulfur.

04:57.631 --> 05:00.748
And you found a goat
tethered to a stake there.

05:00.843 --> 05:02.754
Chupacabra means
“goat-sucker.”

05:02.845 --> 05:07.179
So, for cause of death,
you want me to put down
“goat-sucker”?

05:47.431 --> 05:49.547
Oh! What is that?

05:49.642 --> 05:51.803
The murder victim’s
stomach contents.

05:51.894 --> 05:55.011
Wow. If you’re hungry, there’s
uneaten food in the kitchen.

05:55.105 --> 05:56.686
You’re right. I’m sorry.

05:56.774 --> 05:59.686
There’s just something
about a pregnant woman
that precludes twisted humor.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.438
What’s up?

06:01.529 --> 06:04.441
So, I looked at the clothes
that our guy was wearing.

06:04.532 --> 06:06.739
Apparently, he did not
scrimp on the duds.

06:06.825 --> 06:08.361
Everything was brand-new.

06:08.452 --> 06:10.192
It was like
he was wearing a costume.

06:10.287 --> 06:13.575
So, maybe he wasn’t really
an outdoorsman at all.

06:14.792 --> 06:17.955
Oh, and guess what.
Vincent just apologized to me.

06:18.045 --> 06:20.331
Oh, step number nine—
making amends.

06:20.422 --> 06:24.256
Yeah. He apologized for using
my letter opener to clean
his fingernails.

06:24.385 --> 06:27.798
Ugh!
And for telling his entire darts
team that he slept with me.

06:27.888 --> 06:30.755
Oh, my God!
What is with him?

06:30.891 --> 06:33.428
He was drunk.
Well, but still.

06:33.519 --> 06:35.851
It’s not like I’m gonna
run into his darts team.

06:35.938 --> 06:38.179
Well, you are
a better person than I am.

06:38.274 --> 06:41.812
Really? I’m not gonna forget
that you told me that.

06:43.529 --> 06:45.235
[ Brennan ]
You identified the victim how?

06:45.322 --> 06:48.735
Well, no real hunter
goes out to the woods
in brand-new clothes, right?

06:48.826 --> 06:50.487
So he had to be a tourist,

06:50.578 --> 06:53.866
so I sent his description
to the hotels and lodges
in the area, and I got a hit.

06:53.998 --> 06:56.410
Pine Tree Manor.
Yeah.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.207
They said they had a guest
by the name of Lee Coleman,

06:59.295 --> 07:01.661
who disappeared
and left his stuff behind.

07:03.173 --> 07:05.129
Lee Coleman.

07:07.845 --> 07:09.881
The Lee Coleman.

07:09.972 --> 07:12.839
Why do you keep saying his name
as if! should know him?

07:12.933 --> 07:14.764
Lee Coleman.
K/Y/ the Myth.

07:14.852 --> 07:16.843
It’s a TV show
on the Wilderness Network.

07:16.979 --> 07:19.061
I’ve never seen it.
Wow. Do you even own a TV?

07:19.148 --> 07:21.355
Of course.
It’s in the closet.

07:21.442 --> 07:23.933
Naturally. Anyway, on the show,
Coleman would go out...

07:24.028 --> 07:26.895
and he would debunk
different myths and legends.

07:26.989 --> 07:29.196
You know, the Loch Ness monster,
the yeti,

07:29.283 --> 07:31.069
