disproving because they don’t exist.

07:36.707 --> 07:38.914
Okay, again, just because
you haven’t seen something,

07:39.001 --> 07:40.787
it doesn’t mean
that it doesn’t exist.

07:40.878 --> 07:43.585
I mean, you haven’t seen
the back side of the moon,
but you believe in it.

07:43.714 --> 07:46.751
[ Laughing ]
What?

07:46.842 --> 07:51.256
l was trying to think
of an amusing quip about
the back side of your moon.

07:51.388 --> 07:53.674
[ Laughing ]
All right. Great.

07:53.807 --> 07:57.516
What if Coleman was in the woods
trying to disprove the chupacabra
for K/// the Myth?

07:57.645 --> 07:59.977
And the myth
killed him instead.
It could happen.

08:00.064 --> 08:02.851
No, it couldn’t. You can’t be killed
by something that doesn’t exist.

08:02.941 --> 08:06.354
- You can, if it does exist.
- I don’t think you understand
what the word “myth” means.

08:06.487 --> 08:08.728
[ Exhales ]
[ Laughing ]

08:08.822 --> 08:11.313
[Laughing Harder]

08:12.242 --> 08:13.857
Now what?

08:13.952 --> 08:16.910
Perhaps you could see
your dark side...

08:16.997 --> 08:19.374
if you mooned a mirror.
[Laughs]

08:19.458 --> 08:22.621
Because “moon” is a term
that refers to exposing—

08:22.753 --> 08:24.539
I know, Bones.
Get it?

08:24.672 --> 08:26.833
It’s pretty clever, right?
It’s clever, yeah. Clever.

08:26.924 --> 08:30.041
Yeah, I’d laugh, but, uh, I’m
afraid of driving off the road.

08:30.177 --> 08:32.088
I understand.
You do, right?

08:32.221 --> 08:33.927
Safety first.
Oh, yeah.

08:34.014 --> 08:35.754
I understand.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.259
[Chortling]

08:44.441 --> 08:46.932
[Brennan]
Oh. Huh.

08:48.779 --> 08:52.692
Odd that they would call it
the Pine Tree Manor when it’s
obviously clad in cedar.

08:52.783 --> 08:54.739
I was just thinkin’ that.

08:54.827 --> 08:57.113
Really?
No.

09:00.249 --> 09:01.910
Wow!

09:03.293 --> 09:04.908
- Hello.
- [ Brennan] Hello.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.415
