11:30.148 --> 11:32.480
He made a career
out of making people
look like fools.

11:32.568 --> 11:34.274
Everyone he debunked
probably wanted him dead.

11:34.361 --> 11:37.979
Believers in superstitions like these—
they turn to illogical explanations...

11:38.073 --> 11:41.315
as a way of deriving control
in a frightening and uncertain world.

11:41.410 --> 11:44.743
- They’re nuts.
- That’s a more succinct way
of putting it.

11:44.830 --> 11:48.322
But when a person like that
has his way of life challenged,

11:48.417 --> 11:50.408
becoming violent
would not be surprising.

11:50.502 --> 11:54.211
- You know, Lee was
attacked once... by a dog.
- He debunked a dog?

11:54.298 --> 11:57.665
- What— What was it pretending to be?
- He debunked a pet psychic.

11:57.801 --> 11:59.541
Oh.
She lost a lot of clients.

11:59.636 --> 12:04.005
Um, one day Lee
was coming out of the studio,
and this dog just went for him,

12:04.099 --> 12:06.841
and the pet psychic
was just across the street
watching the whole thing.

12:06.935 --> 12:09.597
- Was it her dog?
- She denied it, but why else
would she be there?

12:09.688 --> 12:11.679
That mutt latched on
to Lee’s leg.

12:11.773 --> 12:14.810
He fell. He broke his ankle,
had to have surgery.

12:14.902 --> 12:17.143
And we couldn’t
even touch the psychic.

12:18.530 --> 12:20.191
- When was this?
- Last year.

12:20.282 --> 12:23.649
- Oh.
- But he insisted on rerunning
the episode two weeks ago.

12:24.828 --> 12:27.285
- He disappeared right after that.
- Yeah.

12:27.372 --> 12:29.704
I told him
he should forget about her.
She’s a loon.

12:29.791 --> 12:32.658
But he wanted
to go after her again.

12:37.758 --> 12:39.965
I’ve never seen bone damage
like this before.

12:40.052 --> 12:43.886
Normally, puncture marks
resulting from carnivorous
scavenging...

12:43.972 --> 12:46.839
are accompanied by pits
in the cortical bone surfaces.

12:46.934 --> 12:48.845
Which are not in evidence.

12:48.936 --> 12:50.847
Mysteriously.

12:50.938 --> 12:54.681
So I’ll analyze the wounds
and try and establish which
were caused by small animals...

12:54.775 --> 12:57.608
and which might’ve been
caused by the chupacabra.

12:57.694 --> 13:01.027
You are not letting
this chupacabra thing go, are ya?

13:01.114 --> 13:04.026
I’d be skeptical if you told me
that there was a venomous,

13:04.117 --> 13:08.030
egg-laying, duck-billed,
beaver-tailed mammal,

13:08.121 --> 13:10.737
and yet the platypus—

13:10.832 --> 13:12.959
it does exist.
[ Sniffing ]

13:13.043 --> 13:17.082
Uh, Mr. Nigel-Murray,
do you need me to take
that alcohol away from you?

13:17.881 --> 13:19.462
Oh! No.
[Chuckles]

13:19.549 --> 13:22.882
No, don’t be absurd.
This is, uh, 80% ethyl alcohol.

13:22.970 --> 13:25.552
I would most likely go blind
if I were to drink this.

13:25.639 --> 13:28.051
lt— Yeah, yeah.
Take it away from me.

13:28.183 --> 13:30.219
Yeah.
Take the top.

13:31.853 --> 13:34.014
Dr. Saroyan.
Sorry.

13:34.106 --> 13:39.021
I really need you to let me
apologize to you,
for my sobriety.

13:41.530 --> 13:43.521
Fine. Shoot.

13:43.615 --> 13:46.652
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.
[Clears Throat]

13:46.743 --> 13:49.325
I once went into your office,
uh, when you weren’t there,

13:49.413 --> 13:52.200
and I noticed
that your desk drawer
was open,

13:52.290 --> 13:55.748
and I saw a stack
of grocery coupons
from the Sunday paper.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.827
Okay. Continue.

13:57.921 --> 13:59.957
And I took
some of the coupons.
[ Clears Throat]

14:00.048 --> 14:03.961
I took— One was for a soda,
and I took another one
for a cheese snack.

14:04.052 --> 14:06.384
And a third was for
a frozen fish dinner.

14:07.431 --> 14:09.467
Three coupons?
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

14:09.558 --> 14:12.265
I was tipsy.

14:12.352 --> 14:15.685
I understand.
And as long as that’s it,
I forgive you.

14:15.772 --> 14:17.728
Um—

14:18.942 --> 14:21.900
What?
I also told some mates
from Paleontology...

14:21.987 --> 14:24.694
that you and I— that
we enjoyed a passionate...

14:24.781 --> 14:28.319
and extremely gymnastic
sexual relationship.

14:28.452 --> 14:30.818
What?
Yes, I did. It’s all true.

14:30.912 --> 14:32.823
I can’t believe
you did that.

14:32.914 --> 14:35.656
l-l know. I know.
And I am deeply,
deeply sorry.

14:35.751 --> 14:37.412
But it was the hooch.

14:38.795 --> 14:42.629
Uh— Oh, forget it.

14:42.716 --> 14:46.925
The injuries on the bones,
I would like an explanation
for them as soon as possible—

14:47.012 --> 14:49.970
one that will not be met
with derision.

14:52.309 --> 14:54.595
I shouldn’t have told her
about the coupons.

14:54.811 --> 14:58.269
I think the victim
is providing
a valuable service...

14:58.398 --> 15:00.775
by debunking
these myths.
Hmm.

15:00.901 --> 15:03.267
[Men Shouting]
Take a look at this.

15:03.361 --> 15:06.649
- This is your proof
- [Shouting in Spanish]

15:06.740 --> 15:08.401
Oh, no.
Don’t be angry at me.

15:08.492 --> 15:11.575
Your priest is the one
who has tricked you. Look.

15:11.661 --> 15:14.368
- / put up a hidden camera—
- [Man]...the deI/i/l

15:14.456 --> 15:17.118
and this is what
it recorded last n/ght.

15:17.209 --> 15:20.292
Your priest has rigged
this statue to cry.

15:20.420 --> 15:25.505
You know, some of these segments
that Coleman recorded
used hidden cameras.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.378
He wouldn’t need
a camera crew.

15:27.469 --> 15:30.302
For his expose on the chupacabra,
he might’ve put up cameras.

15:30.430 --> 15:32.295
They could still be there.
Exactly.

15:32.432 --> 15:36.971
I should watch the show.
You know, not all miracles
are fake, Bones.

15:37.062 --> 15:41.146
Mm-mmm. There’s
a reasonable explanation
for all phenomena.

15:41.233 --> 15:43.394
You know, I saw a yeti.

15:43.485 --> 15:46.022
[Laughs]
Don’t be ridiculous.
Yetis don’t exist.

15:46.863 --> 15:48.603
I was in Nepal.

15:48.698 --> 15:51.110
Rangers have a secure
training base there.

15:51.201 --> 15:54.318
l was doing field exercises,
about to rendezvous
with my platoon,

15:54.412 --> 15:57.199
and... I saw it...

15:57.290 --> 15:59.872
about 30, 35 feet in front of me.

15:59.960 --> 16:02.121
You were in the snow,

16:02.212 --> 16:04.794
in unfamiliar terrain,
alone.

16:04.923 --> 16:07.881
Hallucinations
are common.
It was over 10 feet tall.

16:07.968 --> 16:10.710
It was huge.
I looked straight in its eyes.

16:11.721 --> 16:13.336
I pointed my rifle at it,
and it ran.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.338
This was no hallucination.
Booth.

16:15.433 --> 16:17.924
- I’m sure you thought—
- Okay, why don’t you
just trust me here?

16:18.019 --> 16:21.682
Why can’t you just use
that brilliant scientific mind of yours...

16:21.773 --> 16:24.856
and at least admit
that the possibility...

16:24.943 --> 16:26.899
of what I’m saying here is true?

16:27.988 --> 16:30.320
- You— You’re serious?
- Just forget it.

16:30.407 --> 16:33.570
You know, you talk
a really good game, Bones,
but when it comes down to it,

16:33.660 --> 16:37.653
you’re no different than people
who were certain that the sun
revolved around the Earth.

16:37.747 --> 16:39.999
- That’s not true.
- Hmm.

16:48.633 --> 16:51.295
Well, I did some readings
for Nancy Reagan.

16:51.386 --> 16:54.753
Her dog— a Cavalier
King Charles spaniel, Rex—

16:54.848 --> 16:56.338
cute little thing.

16:56.433 --> 16:59.846
He had some issues with
being in the public eye.
[Laughs]

16:59.978 --> 17:02.594
You can understand.
Sure, sure.

17:02.689 --> 17:05.021
Well, Hobart likes you.

17:05.108 --> 17:07.895
Thinks you have a kind
and understanding face.

17:07.986 --> 17:09.476
- Hobart?
- Hobart.

17:09.571 --> 17:11.857
Hello!
Oh.

17:11.990 --> 17:15.403
Hello.
Hobart looks like
a very nice bird as well.

17:15.535 --> 17:20.199
I wanted to ask you about—
Lee Coleman. I know.
Horrible man.

17:20.290 --> 17:24.124
He has no idea how many animals
he hurt by spreading
those lies about me.

17:24.211 --> 17:27.248
- You were angry about that.
- Well, we all were!

17:27.339 --> 17:31.503
Uh-huh. Well, he thought
you were responsible
for the dog attacking him.

17:31.593 --> 17:33.834
[Laughs]
That’s nonsense.

17:33.970 --> 17:37.053
Hadley acted on his own.
Of course.

17:37.140 --> 17:41.053
But you were with Hadley
when he attacked. I mean,
you could’ve restrained him.

17:41.144 --> 17:44.932
- Well, we were taking a walk.
It all happened very fast.
- Hello!

17:45.023 --> 17:48.060
And he does regret
the pain that he caused.

17:48.151 --> 17:51.359
- He told you that?
- We communicated, yes.

17:51.446 --> 17:53.687
Two weeks ago,
when Lee Coleman was killed,

17:53.782 --> 17:56.148
you were also in West Virginia,
weren’t you?

17:56.243 --> 17:58.905
Yes, I was seeing
a client— a horse.

17:58.995 --> 18:02.453
He felt emotionally displaced
because his owners got a pony.

18:02.540 --> 18:04.371
Well, the farmer
who hired you...

18:04.459 --> 18:06.495
said that you came and went
on your own schedule.

18:08.004 --> 18:10.256
- What are you implying?
- You’re the psychic, Miss Michaels.

18:10.340 --> 18:13.298
I’m sure you can figure it out.
Your business was hurt.

18:13.385 --> 18:16.343
You felt humiliated
and ridiculed.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.010
You wanted revenge.

18:18.098 --> 18:21.556
I did not kill
that dreadful man.

18:21.643 --> 18:23.258
I was at the farm.

18:23.353 --> 18:26.937
Ask the horse, or the chickens.
They all saw me.

18:27.023 --> 18:28.604
Right.

18:28.692 --> 18:31.684
I am not crazy, Dr. Sweets,
and I do want to help.

18:31.778 --> 18:35.817
I heard that you found a goat
at the murder scene.

18:35.949 --> 18:39.237
If you want me
to talk to him.
Nah!

18:39.327 --> 18:41.488
No, thank you,
but thank you.

18:41.621 --> 18:44.363
[Hoban]
Good-bye.
Um, this is getting weird.

18:44.582 --> 18:47.665
So, if Coleman used
a hidden camera out here,

18:47.752 --> 18:50.289
he probably would’ve
had it aimed where
the goat was tethered.

18:50.380 --> 18:52.462
You really had to
volunteer us for this, huh?

18:52.549 --> 18:55.461
Yeah! Thought comin’ out
to the woods would be nice,
you know?

18:55.593 --> 18:58.209
A little fresh air.
Honey, let me share
something with you.

18:58.305 --> 19:00.011
There’s a human
growing inside me.

19:00.098 --> 19:02.885
Vegging on the couch and eating
pints of mint chip ice cream...

19:02.976 --> 19:05.012
is all I actually want to do.

19:05.145 --> 19:09.104
Recent studies show that mothers
who gain excess weight
during pregnancy...

19:09.190 --> 19:11.977
make their babies more prone
to childhood obesity.

19:12.068 --> 19:13.979
Huh. That’s interesting.

19:14.070 --> 19:18.279
I read a study that says
that husbands who suggest
their pregnant wives are fat...

19:18.366 --> 19:21.108
are far more prone
to being slugged by them.

19:21.202 --> 19:23.614
Right. Okay then.

19:23.705 --> 19:26.037
Uh, cameras. Cameras.
Yes.

19:26.124 --> 19:29.116
So I watched the segments
of Kill the Myth that Brennan sent.

19:29.252 --> 19:32.744
Uh-huh.
Coleman always seems to use
the same type of camera.

19:32.839 --> 19:36.423
It’s a fixed-lens infrared
surveillance camera...

19:36.509 --> 19:38.921
with a maximum focal length
of 20 feet.

19:39.012 --> 19:41.424
So then we should
just measure...

19:41.514 --> 19:44.347
a 20-foot perimeter
from the stake...

19:44.434 --> 19:46.015
and then start
searching.

19:46.144 --> 19:48.556
You know what
I don’t understand?
What’s that, babe?

19:48.688 --> 19:53.307
How come a creature
whose name means “goat-sucker”
didn’t suck the goat?

19:53.401 --> 19:57.235
[ Scoffs ]
Because there’s no such
thing as a chupacabra.

19:57.322 --> 20:00.280
Oh, this coming from the woman that
believes the stars control our fates.

20:00.367 --> 20:03.359
Of course you’re going
to belittle astrology.
You’re a Virgo.

20:03.453 --> 20:05.785
I think I got something.

20:07.957 --> 20:09.993
Well, h-how are we
gonna get up there?

20:10.085 --> 20:11.916
Well, it’s just
a little tree.

20:12.003 --> 20:14.335
Hey, babe, you’re going
to be a father.

20:14.422 --> 20:16.413
I don’t want anything
to happen to you.

20:16.508 --> 20:18.920
Okay. But please—
Please be careful.

20:19.636 --> 20:21.297
Okay.

20:22.972 --> 20:25.304
- Got it.
- Hold on tight.

20:25.392 --> 20:27.508
All right.
I’m gonna throw this
down to you, okay?

20:27.602 --> 20:29.103
Yeah.

20:31.481 --> 20:34.393
Got it. Um, it looks like
there’s some water damage,

20:34.484 --> 20:37.726
but I might be able to recover
some data from the memory card.

20:37.821 --> 20:39.527
Uh-huh.

20:39.614 --> 20:41.570
If this time stamp is correct,

20:41.658 --> 20:44.274
this was taken on the night
that Lee Coleman was killed.

20:45.787 --> 20:48.153
He might have recorded
his own murder.

20:57.382 --> 20:59.247
This is the original image...

20:59.342 --> 21:02.459
of the damage done
to the victim’s ribs and torso.

21:02.554 --> 21:07.344
Now here I’ve eliminated
all injuries caused from
postmortem scavenging,

21:07.434 --> 21:10.676
leaving only the wounds
incurred during
the initial attack.

21:11.604 --> 21:13.219
What is this triangle?

21:13.314 --> 21:14.929
That is a bite mark,

21:15.024 --> 21:19.984
presumably the result
of two upper incisors
and a single lower incisor.

21:20.071 --> 21:23.529
I’m not familiar with any animal
with that configuration of teeth.

21:23.616 --> 21:25.698
Like that.

21:27.245 --> 21:29.782
Legend says that that
is how the goat-sucker...

21:29.873 --> 21:31.534
drains blood from its prey.

21:31.624 --> 21:34.741
Hodgins is analyzing the swab
from the injury site.

21:34.836 --> 21:37.748
We’ll see what he comes up with
that doesn’t rely on legend.

21:37.839 --> 21:40.205
I— I’m very, very sorry.

21:40.300 --> 21:42.586
Why? You’ve done more
than satisfactory work.

21:42.677 --> 21:44.292
Oh! No, no, no, no.

21:44.387 --> 21:48.676
As part of my recovery,
uh, for drinking a lot
and having fun,

21:48.766 --> 21:50.427
I have to make amends.

21:50.518 --> 21:52.895
All right. What for?

21:52.979 --> 21:55.516
One night,
I borrowed your iguana...

21:55.607 --> 21:59.225
and wore it as a hat
at a party.

22:00.820 --> 22:04.062
Well, you must’ve taken care of him,
because I didn’t see any damage.

22:04.157 --> 22:06.443
And also I have
to apologize, um,

22:06.534 --> 22:09.321
for spreading a rumor—
[ Chuckles ]

22:09.412 --> 22:11.744
that you and l were lovers.

22:11.831 --> 22:15.039
But it was nothing serious.
We were on and off.

22:15.126 --> 22:17.868
We were just each other’s
sexual playthings.

22:17.962 --> 22:21.921
And please remember
that I’m apologizing
for things that I did...

22:22.008 --> 22:24.090
when l was besotted
with drink.

22:24.177 --> 22:27.260
[ Loud Laughing]

22:27.347 --> 22:28.962
Why are you laughing?

22:29.057 --> 22:33.926
The absurdity
of you and I having...

22:34.020 --> 22:37.478
a sexual relationship
of any kind.

22:37.565 --> 22:41.433
I mean, your— your friends
must be very gullible.

22:41.528 --> 22:43.359
No, they’re not—
not particularly.

22:43.446 --> 22:48.190
Then they must’ve been inebriated
and incapable of rational thought.

22:48.284 --> 22:50.570
Stranger things
have happened.

22:50.662 --> 22:52.653
[Laughs]
I can’t think of any.

22:52.747 --> 22:55.989
l-l mean,
I would sooner confirm...

22:56.084 --> 22:59.292
that the chupacabra was
the cause of this man’s death.

22:59.379 --> 23:02.337
I’ve been told I’m an—
I’m an excellent lover.

23:05.969 --> 23:07.550
So—

23:09.055 --> 23:12.047
- It appears that
I’ve hurt your feelings.
- No. No, no.

23:12.141 --> 23:14.757
It’s— It’s all part
of the process,

23:14.852 --> 23:19.687
and l have to accept
the consequences of my actions
as part of my recovery.

23:19.774 --> 23:21.685
Then I’m glad
that I could help.

23:21.776 --> 23:24.893
I-I must say that I’m impressed
that you were able to get my iguana...

23:24.988 --> 23:26.899
to stay on top of your head.

23:26.990 --> 23:29.322
I’m clever with ribbons.

23:33.413 --> 23:35.199
Here you go.

23:35.290 --> 23:36.700
[ Knocking ]

23:36.791 --> 23:38.747
I’m so sorry to bother you,
Agent Booth,

23:38.835 --> 23:40.700
but I really need to talk to you
about Lee Coleman’s murder.

23:40.795 --> 23:42.501
Sure. Come on in.
No problem.

23:42.589 --> 23:44.250
Have a seat.

23:44.340 --> 23:48.333
I started thinking
that if someone killed Lee,
I could be next.

23:48.469 --> 23:51.427
You?
Maybe I’m crazy, but before
I produced Lee’s show,

23:51.514 --> 23:53.470
I worked with a man
named Terry Bemis.

23:53.558 --> 23:55.014
Okay. Who’s Terry Bemis?

23:55.101 --> 23:57.683
He had a show
on the Wilderness Network,
Seeing is Belle I/ing.

23:57.770 --> 24:00.512
He’s probably the most famous
cryptozoologist in the country.

24:00.607 --> 24:03.644
That’s very impressive,
but, uh, I don’t know
what that means.

24:03.735 --> 24:06.272
Cryptozoology is the study
of hidden animals,

24:06.362 --> 24:08.353
animals whose very existence
is in doubt.

24:08.448 --> 24:10.939
Oh, right.
Like the chupacabra.

24:11.034 --> 24:12.570
Yes. Sure.

24:12.660 --> 24:16.198
But also various sea animals
who’ve actually been
found and confirmed.

24:16.289 --> 24:20.032
Look, the point is that, um,
Lee got Terry booted off
the Wilderness Network.

24:20.126 --> 24:22.458
Oh, so you left crypto guy
and you went with Lee.

24:22.545 --> 24:24.456
Yes. The network wanted me to.

24:24.547 --> 24:27.459
Terry was very angry,
as you would expect.
[ Latches Click Open ]

24:27.550 --> 24:30.462
He started making threats,
which I didn’t believe at the time.

24:30.553 --> 24:32.965
But I did get
this e-mail yesterday.

24:34.474 --> 24:38.808
“Heard about Lee.
Some people get what
they deserve, I guess.

24:38.895 --> 24:41.352
Wonder how things
will turn out for you.”

24:43.483 --> 24:47.897
- Do you know where I
can find Terry Bemis now?
- Where else? Public access.

24:51.282 --> 24:55.150
[Angela ] This is the footage
from the hidden camera
we found in the tree.

24:55.244 --> 24:58.486
Oh, my goat friend and l
have been waiting here
for e/ght hours.

24:58.581 --> 25:01.539
The only thing
we ’I/e been attacked by
are mosquitoes,

25:01.626 --> 25:06.620
which is strange because
if these woods are supposedly
riddled with chupacabra,

25:06.714 --> 25:08.625
you would expect
at least one of them. ..

25:08.716 --> 25:12.129
to jump on the only goat
within a hundred-mile radius.

25:12.220 --> 25:15.178
What he’s saying makes sense,
but he’s really unlikable.

25:15.264 --> 25:18.256
Well— [Laughing]
sun’s gonna be up soon.

25:18.351 --> 25:22.139
And since these creatures
are supposedly nocturnal,

25:22.230 --> 25:25.939
B/l/y Goat Gruffand/
m/ght as well call it a night.

25:27.443 --> 25:30.230
Nothing for us there.
Well, that’s what
I thought at first too.

25:30.321 --> 25:31.936
But check this out.

25:32.073 --> 25:34.564
[Beep/'ng]
Okay, here it is.

25:34.659 --> 25:36.149
What?

25:36.244 --> 25:39.782
Look at the goat’s ears
just before Coleman
shuts off the camera.

25:42.250 --> 25:44.241
Oh, wow.
He heard something.

25:44.335 --> 25:46.166
Mm-hmm. Something
Coleman didn’t hear.

25:46.254 --> 25:49.041
Can you work
some sort of audio magic,
see if you can pick it up?

25:49.132 --> 25:51.748
Yeah, it’s worth a try.

25:51.843 --> 25:53.879
[ Beeping ]

25:58.349 --> 26:01.341
[Electronic Chirping ]

26:02.478 --> 26:05.060
[ Faint Rambling;
Chirping Continues]

26:05.148 --> 26:08.811
Did a G.C.-mass spec
on the swab results from
our little triangular bite.

26:08.901 --> 26:11.563
I expected to find saliva,
but instead I got that.

26:11.654 --> 26:15.317
“Bisphenol A,
diethyl propane
and amorphous silica.”

26:15.450 --> 26:17.111
[ Device Beeps ]
What is that?

26:17.201 --> 26:20.614
No clue. But as much
as it pains me to say it, it’s
probably not chupacabra spit.

26:20.705 --> 26:23.287
Did you ID. the dermis
and those needles
we found on the body?

26:23.374 --> 26:26.832
Yeah, I did.
The reptile scales belong
to a Ctenosaura pectinata,

26:26.919 --> 26:28.875
or Mexican spiny-tailed iguana.

26:28.963 --> 26:32.547
And the needles,
the needles are
from a wild boar.

26:32.675 --> 26:35.382
Are those rare?
No, not anywhere
you can buy a hairbrush.

26:35.470 --> 26:37.961
This seems to be shaping up
to be nothing more than a hoax.

26:38.097 --> 26:42.136
Don’t sound so sad.
Do you really wanna live in a world
where chupacabras roam free?

26:42.226 --> 26:43.841
Yes, I really do.

26:48.983 --> 26:51.269
So, our friend,
the animal psychic,
has an alibi.

26:51.360 --> 26:53.351
Ha-ha! Don’t tell me.

26:53.446 --> 26:57.689
She was feeding a flock
of pigeons in the park, and
they’re all willing to testify.

26:57.825 --> 27:00.316
Close.
Counseling a horse.
I was making a joke.

27:00.411 --> 27:03.528
I know. Still, just afraid
of driving off the road.
You know, great.

27:03.623 --> 27:05.955
Anyway, the horse’s owner
placed her on the farm.

27:06.042 --> 27:07.703
Oh.

27:09.253 --> 27:11.460
I did some research.
Really?

27:11.547 --> 27:14.880
The tracks you saw in Nepal
are easily explained.

27:14.967 --> 27:19.085
I believe they were the tracks
of smaller animals widened
by the afternoon sun.

27:19.180 --> 27:22.843
I didn’t see just tracks. I saw
the Abominable Snowman himself.

27:22.934 --> 27:24.925
Hmm? He looked at me,
and I looked at him.

27:25.019 --> 27:27.385
I believe you saw
what you say you saw.

27:27.480 --> 27:30.267
- But you believe
it was a hallucination?
- I believe you actually saw it.

27:30.358 --> 27:32.644
Ah. A yeti?
No.

27:32.735 --> 27:37.479
What you saw was
Ursus arctos isabe/linus.

27:37.573 --> 27:40.360
They’re usually red
or sandy in color,

27:40.451 --> 27:42.487
but the one you saw
was covered in ice.

27:42.620 --> 27:44.861
A seven-foot bear
covered in ice?
Yes.

27:44.956 --> 27:49.495
Ursus arctos
makes a sound much like
a human being grunting.

27:49.585 --> 27:51.541
You did a lot
of work on this.

27:51.629 --> 27:55.463
Yes. I believe you saw
exactly what you say you saw.

27:55.591 --> 27:58.879
You’re simply calling it
by the wrong name.
Ah, thank you, Bones.

27:58.970 --> 28:01.586
I appreciate you, you know,
giving me the benefit of the doubt.

28:01.681 --> 28:03.421
You’re welcome.

28:09.981 --> 28:11.846
Okay, look, this guy’s
got two motives.

28:11.941 --> 28:14.523
Okay. One, revenge
for getting booted
to public access.

28:14.610 --> 28:18.273
And two,
he earns a living talking
about mythical animals.

28:18.364 --> 28:20.980
Also, he’d be an expert
at faking a chupacabra attack.

28:21.075 --> 28:23.031
[ Man ]
Three, two, one.

28:23.119 --> 28:26.111
I received word this week
that there was a sighting...

28:26.205 --> 28:29.368
of one of the most
elusive cryptids—

28:29.458 --> 28:31.995
the Bukit Timah Monkey Man,

28:32.086 --> 28:35.624
an immortal hominid that lives
in the forests of Singapore.

28:37.884 --> 28:39.715
What more proof
do you need?

28:39.802 --> 28:42.043
Well, this is a treat.

28:42.138 --> 28:44.424
It looks like we’re
being joined today...

28:44.515 --> 28:47.302
by one of the many
celebrity guest scientists...

28:47.393 --> 28:50.180
who frequently appear
on Seeing is Believing.

28:50.271 --> 28:54.014
Forensic anthropologist
Dr. Temperance Brennan is here.

28:54.108 --> 28:55.848
Please, join me, Doctor.

28:56.694 --> 28:58.730
Kevin, get a chair!

28:58.821 --> 29:01.984
- Should I go?
- Why not? It’s not like
anybody’s watching.

29:03.618 --> 29:05.779
Just set it there.
Hello.
[ Clears Throat]

29:05.870 --> 29:07.326
Bup,bup,bup,
bup,bup.

29:07.455 --> 29:09.446
Hello! Welcome.
Thank you.

29:09.540 --> 29:13.954
It is always a pleasure
to meet a fellow scientist.

